<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06183166 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06183166 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  The African National Congress, convening inside South Africa for the firsttime in more than 30 years, will choose new leaders this week and shape itsprogram for negotiating the future. At least 2,000 delegates will gather inthe Indian Ocean city of Durban on Tuesday for the 48th conference of thenation's largest black opposition group. It comes at a time of black factionalfighting that prompted the ANC to halt talks with the white government,accusing the authorities of deliberately failing to stop the violence.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  ANC SET TO CONVENE TUESDAY IN S. AFRICA  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Foreign News in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910701  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  July  </MONTH><PG.COL>  6A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  91  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday July 1, 199100183166,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>